When this error message is triggered, I get a protobuf exception, apparently because the response message hasn't been filled out:

~~~
[Err] [HaptixWorldPlugin.cc:648] Model not found: green_cricket_ball
[libprotobuf FATAL google/protobuf/message_lite.cc:273] CHECK failed: IsInitialized(): Can't serialize message of type "haptix.comm.msgs.hxModel" because it is missing required fields: name, transform, id, gravity_mode
terminate called after throwing an instance of 'google::protobuf::FatalException'
  what():  CHECK failed: IsInitialized(): Can't serialize message of type "haptix.comm.msgs.hxModel" because it is missing required fields: name, transform, id, gravity_mode
~~~
